  <h3>Implementation Approach</h3>

  <h4>Phase 1: Document Intelligence Pipeline</h4>
  <p>
    We built a sophisticated document processing pipeline that handles multiple document types:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>OCR & Text Extraction:</strong> High-accuracy extraction from scanned documents, faxes, and PDFs</li>
    <li><strong>Document Classification:</strong> Automatic identification of document types (medical records, invoices, EOBs)</li>
    <li><strong>Entity Extraction:</strong> Extraction of key fields like patient info, diagnosis codes, procedure codes, and amounts</li>
    <li><strong>Cross-Document Validation:</strong> Automatic verification that information is consistent across all claim documents</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Phase 2: AI Decision Engine</h4>
  <p>
    The core AI engine evaluates claims against policy rules and historical patterns:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Policy Compliance Check:</strong> Automatic verification against coverage rules and exclusions</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Necessity Review:</strong> AI-assisted evaluation of treatment appropriateness</li>
    <li><strong>Fraud Detection:</strong> Pattern analysis to flag suspicious claims for review</li>
    <li><strong>Auto-Adjudication:</strong> Automatic approval of straightforward claims meeting all criteria</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Phase 3: Human-in-the-Loop Workflow</h4>
  <p>
    Not all claims can be fully automated. We designed an intelligent routing system:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Confidence Scoring:</strong> Each decision includes a confidence score</li>
    <li><strong>Smart Routing:</strong> Low-confidence claims routed to appropriate specialists</li>
    <li><strong>Assisted Review:</strong> AI provides recommendations and highlights key information for human reviewers</li>
    <li><strong>Continuous Learning:</strong> Human decisions feed back to improve model accuracy</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Technical Architecture</h3>
  <p>
    The solution runs on AWS with a microservices architecture designed for scalability and reliability:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Ingestion Layer:</strong> S3 + Lambda for document intake from multiple channels</li>
    <li><strong>Processing Layer:</strong> EKS-hosted microservices for document processing</li>
    <li><strong>AI Layer:</strong> SageMaker endpoints for custom models + OpenAI API for GPT-4</li>
    <li><strong>Data Layer:</strong> Aurora PostgreSQL for structured data, OpenSearch for document search</li>
    <li><strong>Integration Layer:</strong> API Gateway + custom connectors for legacy systems</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Security & Compliance</h3>
  <p>
    Healthcare data requires the highest security standards. Our implementation includes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>HIPAA-compliant infrastructure with BAA from all vendors</li>
    <li>End-to-end encryption for data at rest and in transit</li>
    <li>Role-based access controls with audit logging</li>
    <li>PHI data masking in non-production environments</li>
    <li>Regular penetration testing and security audits</li>
  </ul>

